Description: Fragment of flattened handle of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora at neck join, gradual curve. Clay fine light beige-brown; cream slip. Rectangular stamp.
Production date: 211 BC (see N. Badoud, Le temps de Rhodes (2015) 142.)
Curator's comments: Petrie Diary (EES Archive XVII 47) p. 128, 8. Name Xenostratos. From the same die as a piece from Miletus, MAS255.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0664)
